info.description: Run Llama locally through Ollama. # Ollama 1. [Download Ollama and install Ollama for Mac, Linux, and Windows](https://ollama.com/) 2. `$ ollama pull Llama3.1:Latest` (this will take time, the smallest Llama3.1 model is >4G. 3. If you want to run and interact with `Llama3.1:Latest`in the terminal, run the following command:`$ ollama run llama3.1:latest` 4. To run the API and use in Postman, run `ollama serve` and you'll start a new server. You'll need to copy/paste the `OLLAMA_HOST` into the variables in this collection, or create a new global variable. 5. Go to `POST` request: [Chat Completion (non-streaming)](https://ai-on-postman.postman.co/workspace/Ollama~b714ac52-0766-4540-bb03-46d82bf23114/request/37636463-8272959d-d651-4901-880c-b7561692b380?action=share&source=copy-link&creator=37636463) 6. In the "Body" tab, update the variable `{{prompt}}` ## Streaming The only difference between streaming and non-streaming is the including of the param `"streaming": false` as part of the body. If you wish to use streaming, omit the param and you'll receive a large JSON object with the individually streamed items. We have created a script that collects the stream and outputs it as a `console.log`. (See image below) # Troubleshooting - Error: `command not found: ollama` - Solution: If you've downloaded the app, you likely need to move it out from the downloads folder to your Applications (or similar) folder - Error: `$ Error: listen tcp 127.0.0.1:11434: bind: address already in use` after running `ollama serve` - Solution: run `$ export OLLAMA_HOST=127.0.0.1:3000` then run `ollama serve` again. - `ollama serve --help` is your best friend.

request.description:
## Mistral:Latest

1. [Download Ollama and install Ollama for Mac, Linux, and Windows](https://ollama.com/)
    
2. `$ ollama pull mistral:latest`
    
3. If you want to run and interact with `mistral:latest`in the terminal, run the following command:`$ ollama run mistral:latest`
    
4. To run the API and use in Postman, run `ollama serve` and you'll start a new server. You'll need to copy/paste the `OLLAMA_HOST` into the variables in this collection, or create a new global variable.
    
5. In the "Body" tab, update the variable `{{prompt}}`
    
6. Send the request!
    
    1. This is running Mistral on your machine. Depending on your hardware, this may take multiple minutes to complete.

## Mistral:Latest (streaming)

item.name: Model

request.description:
Create a model from a local [Modefile](https://github.com/jmorganca/ollama/blob/main/docs/modelfile.md)

Modelfile must be in a location `ollama` has permission to access.

A stream of JSON objects is returned. When finished, `status` is `success`.

**Parameters**

You can add `"stream": false` to the body to get a chunked rather than streamed response.

**Example Modelfile**

```
FROM llama2
# sets the temperature to 1 [higher is more creative, lower is more coherent]
PARAMETER temperature 1
# sets the context window size to 4096, this controls how many tokens the LLM can use as context to generate the next token
PARAMETER num_ctx 4096
# sets a custom system prompt to specify the behavior of the chat assistant
SYSTEM You are Mario from super mario bros, acting as an assistant.

 ```

response.name: 200 - create (streamed)

request.description:
You can use your custom created model by name, the same way you use other downloaded models from the `/api/generate` endpoint

The example shown here uses a model built with the following Modelfile:

```
FROM llama2
# sets the temperature to 1 [higher is more creative, lower is more coherent]
PARAMETER temperature 1
# sets the context window size to 4096, this controls how many tokens the LLM can use as context to generate the next token
PARAMETER num_ctx 4096
# sets a custom system prompt to specify the behavior of the chat assistant
SYSTEM You are Mario from super mario bros, acting as an assistant.


 ```

request.description:
Pull a model from the [Ollama library](https://ollama.ai/library)

**Parameters**

You can add `"stream": false` to the body to get a chunked response instead of streamed
Upload a model to a model library. Requires registering for ollama.ai and adding a public key first.

In LLMs, embeddings are numerical representations of words, phrases, or sentences that capture their meaning and context

### Parameters

- `model`: name of model to generate embeddings from
- `prompt`: text to generate embeddings for
    

Advanced parameters:

- `options`: additional model parameters listed in the documentation for the [Modelfile](https://github.com/jmorganca/ollama/blob/main/docs/modelfile.md#valid-parameters-and-values) such as `temperature`

item.description: These APIs are like "Admin" APIs, which are used for managing the local models on your machine. You can get local models that have been downloaded on your machine, see a list of all the running models (when you use `ollama serve`), pull new models, get model information, and more.
